comments.body:
I've updated `lib-proc6` so it now has 8 cores. It still runs 5 processes. 

Looking at our Sidekiq setup, there are three more Sidekiq VMs in the other VMCluster. Stats on those three:

lib-proc7: 2 cores, 5 processes
lib-proc10: 2 cores, 5 processes
lib-proc11: 2 cores, 5 processes

All 6 VMs are configured to run jobs from all queues (high, default, low, and super-low). If we continue to see issues around background jobs, we might need to add more resources to the other 3 VMs and/or configure the less-beefy machines to run the lower-priority jobs.

For now, however, we have stability with the additional resources on lib-proc6. Closing with the knowledge that we may need to reopen in future . . .
